## Exercise 2: Beeper Inverter

Invert the beeper pattern across the entire row:
- If a position has a beeper → pick it up
- If a position has no beeper → put one down

The starting pattern has beepers at positions 1, 3, and 5. After your program runs, beepers should be at positions 2 and 4 instead.

<KarelEnvironment config={exercise2Config} />

---

## Exercise 3: Wall Navigator

Navigate Karel from (1, 1) to the beeper at (5, 5) — but there are walls in the way!

You'll need to use sensors to detect walls and choose alternate paths. One strategy: try to move east; if blocked, try north. Use a combination of while loops, if/else, and sensor functions.

> **Hint:** All the sensors are available for this exercise. Use `front_is_clear()` to check before moving, and `turn_left()` to try a different direction when blocked.

<KarelEnvironment config={exercise3Config} />

